<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,327,535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,400,426]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Remarks.</emphasis>
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[473,555,400,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1900,1925]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,569,1863]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,561,1875]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. Habitus of species of Geodromicus: 13–G. chinensis (Zhejiang), 14–G. cupreostigma (Hubei). Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884798" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884798/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
. Male abdominal tergite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[945,1026,399,426]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[217,1364,561,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1374,556,1949]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Male of Geodromicus chinensis (Zhejiang): 15–abdominal tergite VIII, 16–abdominal sternite VIII, 17–aedeagus, dorsal view, 18–aedeagus, lateral view, 19–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
, and male abdominal sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[179,260,436,462]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[217,1364,561,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1374,556,1949]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Male of Geodromicus chinensis (Zhejiang): 15–abdominal tergite VIII, 16–abdominal sternite VIII, 17–aedeagus, dorsal view, 18–aedeagus, lateral view, 19–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[441,574,436,462]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–19" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1999]" captionTargetBox="[217,1364,561,1944]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[214,1374,556,1949]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15–19. Male of Geodromicus chinensis (Zhejiang): 15–abdominal tergite VIII, 16–abdominal sternite VIII, 17–aedeagus, dorsal view, 18–aedeagus, lateral view, 19–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884802" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884802/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Figs. 17–19</figureCitation>
. Previously, the species was known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[1128,1176,437,463]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
material from ‘Provinz Fukien (Foochow)’, 
<collectingRegion box="[386,458,472,498]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Fujian</collectingRegion>
(Bernhauer 1938; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V." box="[674,831,472,498]" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" pagination="151 - 190" refId="ref19571" refString="Shavrin, A. V. (2018) The lestevoides species group of the genus Geodromicus Redtenbacher, 1857 (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae). Zootaxa, 4378 (2), 151 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4378.2.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Shavrin 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bernhauer" authorityYear="1938" box="[1073,1213,472,499]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis">
<emphasis box="[1073,1093,473,499]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1109,1213,472,498]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">chinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1253,1320,472,498]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">China</collectingCountry>
as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 113" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 113. Distribution of 21 species of Geodromicus in China: 1–G. abdominalis, 2–G. amplissimus, 3–G. aokii, 4–G. beibienkoi, 5–G. chinensis, 6–G. cupreostigma, 7–G. formosanus, 8–G. frigidus, 9–G. hammondi, 10–G. lestevoides, 11–G. magnus sp. n., 12–G. namucuoicus sp. n., 13–G. ohkurai, 14–G. philydroides, 15–G. shii sp. n., 16–G. sibiricus, 17–G. sinuatocollis, 18–G. sinuatus, 19–G. smetanai, 20–G. subquadratus sp. n., 21–G. taiwanensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884852/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Fig. 113</figureCitation>
. It is here recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[477,577,508,534]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="6" pageNumber="138">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
